# Per-machine environment for the game-shell input daemon.
#
# Copy to ~/.config/game-shell/daemon.env and edit. game-shell-session.sh
# sources this file (set -a) before starting the daemon, so every uncommented
# line below becomes an environment variable the daemon reads. Everything here
# is OPTIONAL — with no daemon.env the shell still boots; these vars only turn
# on the LAN control surface and the optional Plex / Steam home-screen widgets.
#
# Keep this file readable only by you (chmod 600) — it can hold bearer tokens.

# --- LAN control surface (HTTP bridge) ---------------------------------------
# Bind address for the HTTP/1.1 control bridge (GET /screenshot, POST intents).
# Empty / unset = bridge off. Use 127.0.0.1:8089 for local-only, or
# 0.0.0.0:8089 to expose it on the LAN (firewall it yourself).
#GAME_SHELL_HTTP_BIND=127.0.0.1:8089

# Require a bearer token on the HTTP bridge + MCP server. Default true whenever
# a bind is set. Only set false on a trusted, firewalled LAN.
#GAME_SHELL_HTTP_AUTH_ENABLED=true

# Shared bearer token for the HTTP bridge and MCP server (required when
# GAME_SHELL_HTTP_AUTH_ENABLED=true). Generate one: `openssl rand -hex 32`.
#GAME_SHELL_HTTP_TOKEN=replace-with-a-long-random-token

# --- MCP server (optional, requires the daemon built with --features mcp) -----
# Streamable-HTTP MCP endpoint at /mcp exposing the daemon's control surface as
# tools. Empty / unset = off. Shares the HTTP bridge's auth/token vars above.
#GAME_SHELL_MCP_BIND=127.0.0.1:8090
# Enable the dev tool surface (build/restart/deploy). Leave off in production.
#GAME_SHELL_MCP_DEV=1
# Comma-separated Host header allowlist for the MCP server (DNS-rebinding guard).
#GAME_SHELL_MCP_ALLOWED_HOSTS=localhost,my-host.local

# --- HDMI-CEC lifecycle (optional, requires the daemon built with --features cec)
# Daemon wakes the AV chain on start/resume and standbys it on suspend.
#GAME_SHELL_CEC_LIFECYCLE=1

# --- Plex home-screen widget (optional) --------------------------------------
# On Deck / Recently Added hubs on the home screen. BOTH are required or the
# widget collapses even when toggled on in settings.
#GAME_SHELL_PLEX_URL=http://plex-host:32400
#GAME_SHELL_PLEX_TOKEN=your-plex-token

# --- Steam library row (optional) --------------------------------------------
# Points at a game-shell-host sidecar (see docs/HOST_SETUP.md) running on the
# gaming PC to enumerate and launch installed Steam games. BOTH are required or
# the Steam row collapses; the token must match the host's GAME_SHELL_HOST_TOKEN.
#GAME_SHELL_STEAM_URL=http://gaming-pc:47995
#GAME_SHELL_STEAM_TOKEN=must-match-host-token
